- Load dialog should immediately load after system dialog returns selection
- Load dialog should allow up and down arrows
- beat analysis shows possible beats (and eventually drum voices like snare, kick, tom, etc) on spectrogram
  - makes it easy to select a range of spectrogram, get suggested beats, and put them in
- section duplicate tool:
  - duplicates the beat pattern and measures of a given section (e.g. verse)
  - the new pasted section can be dragged on the timeline,
  - but analysis tools help match its structure to the underlying audio (i.e. find and fix to the right beats)
  - bonus: automatically find verse 2 from verse 1.
- better bulk insertion
  - global BPM inference range setting (e.g. 50 to 180bpm)
  - audio analysis for suggested beats
  - mark beginning and end of section, offer subdivision choice 2=100bpm,3,4=200bpm,5
  - reinterpolate beats between (delete and reinsert)
  - insert measure(s) 4,8,12 beats
- Chord progressions per section
- Lyric editing:
  Add an editor timeline pane similar to the section editor pane, for editing lyrics.
  A lyric line is a selection that includes editable text.
  Lyrics are stored in the timeseries file as "lyric: text" lines and have a start and end time just like sections.
- Bulk lyric insertion / editing:
  A dialog that allows pasting in multiple lines of text (e.g. copied from a webpage).
  Lyrics are broken into lyric sections per line of text.
  A fuzzy, somewhat smart parser can take a cut-and-pasted bulk text and line up lyrics with the sections they are contained in, e.g. paste in:

[Verse 1]
There's a lady who's sure all that glitters is gold
And she's buying a stairway to Heaven
When she gets there, she knows if the stores are all closed
With a word, she can get what she came for
Ooh, and she's buying a stairway to Heaven

[Verse 2]
There's a sign on the wall, but she wants to be sure
'Cause you know sometimes words have two meanings
In a tree by the brook, there's a songbird who sings
Sometimes all of our thoughts are misgiven

[Refrain]
Ooh, it makes me wonder
Ooh, makes me wonder

  Stretch: this representation is editable and kept in correspondence with the timeline; lyrics are displayed/editable as a combined simple text file; when editing the current line highlights the section it is in and the lyric line.
  TBD: Beat-precise lyrics. In the lyric editing timeline pane, there is a way to line up beats with individual words and syllables.
- Riff text

